132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 606
H.P. 374 House of Representatives, February 25, 2025
Resolve, to Study Barriers to Financial Assistance Programs for
Farmers and Food Producers
Received by the Clerk of the House on February 20, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed
pursuant to Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative PLUECKER of Warren.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Sec. 1. Commissioner of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry to seek
2 stakeholder input on lowering barriers to financial assistance programs.
3 Resolved: That the Commissioner of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry shall direct
4 staff of the Bureau of Agriculture, Food and Rural Resources to study the bureau's financial
5 assistance programs for farmers and food producers to identify barriers to these programs
6 and methods to eliminate those barriers and increase the effectiveness of the programs in
7 addressing farmer and food producer needs. This study must be undertaken within existing
8 resources and must include at least 2 listening sessions with farmers and food producers.
9 The listening sessions must encompass topics, including, but not limited to, the following:
10 1. Application materials, submission procedures and timelines for application retention
11 by the Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry;
12 2. Contact procedures to inform applicants of new program opportunities;
13 3. Accessibility for beginning and emerging farmers and the expansion of education
14 about department programs, partnerships with community organizations to reach new
15 groups of farmers and identification of farmers who currently underuse department
16 programs; and
17 4. Input on how the department can organize and consolidate its financial assistance
18 offerings.
19 Sec. 2. Report. Resolved: That, by January 15, 2026, the Commissioner of
20 Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry shall submit a report detailing the results of the
21 study under section 1 and any recommended legislation to the Joint Standing Committee
22 on Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry, which may report out legislation to the Second
23 Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.
24 SUMMARY
2255 This resolve requires the Commissioner of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry to
2266 direct staff of the Bureau of Agriculture, Food and Rural Resources to study the bureau's
2277 financial assistance programs for farmers and food producers to identify barriers to these
2288 programs and methods to eliminate those barriers and increase the effectiveness of the
2299 programs in addressing farmer and food producer needs. The commissioner is required to
3300 submit a report by January 15, 2026 to the Joint Standing Committee on Agriculture,
3311 Conservation and Forestry, which may report out legislation to the Second Regular Session
3322 of the 132nd Legislature.
